Pour @cold salted water{300%ml} into a #medium pot{} with a tight-fitting lid.
Stir in the @rice{150%g} and bring to the boil.

Once boiling, lower the heat to medium, cover, and cook for ~{10%minutes}.
Remove from the heat.

Keep covered for ~{10%minutes} or until ready to serve (the rice will continue
to cook in its own steam).

Halve the @bell pepper{1} and discard the core and seeds. Chop into 2cm chunks.

Halve, peel and thinly slice the @shallot{1}.

Drain and rinse the @black beans{1%pack} in a #sieve{}.

Place a #pan{} over medium-high heat with a drizzle of @oil{to taste}.

Add the shallot and bell pepper. Cook until softened, ~{4-5%minutes}.

Pop in the @Mexican style spice mix{2%sachets} and fry for ~{1%minute} more.

Next add the @tomato paste{1%tin}, beans, @vegetable stock{1%sachet}, @sugar{1/2%tsp}
and @water{100%ml}.

> Double both water and sugar for 4 servings.

Cover and simmer for ~{4-5%minutes}.

Meanwhile, trim and thinly slice the @scallion{2}.

In a #small bowl{} mix half the @chipotle paste{2%sachets} with the @aioli{1%sachet}.

Once the pepper has softened, remove the pan from the heat.

Mix in the remaining chipotle paste and a knob of @butter{1%to taste}.

Add a splash of water if you feel the sauce needs loosening. Season to taste
with @salt{to taste}, @pepper{to taste} and @sugar{to taste}.

Scatter over the @grated cheese{50%g} and keep the pan covered for ~{1-2%minutes}
to allow the cheese to melt.

Fluff up the rice with a #fork{} and divide between bowls.

Top with cheesy Mexican spiced veg.

Drizzle over the @BBQ sauce{2%sachets}.

Finish with a scattering of sliced scallion.